                "Uncertainty of the net peak area ratio",
                " (I13/I12) which includes:"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the statistical uncertainty dominated by the",
                "13C(n,alpha0)10Be statistics, 5.9% at 14.3MeV with",
                " 291 counts, 4.0% at 17.0MeV with 635 counts;"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the uncertainty introduced by the analysis",
                "method, dominated by the pulse width selection,",
                "estimated as a ratio of the 0.1 ns sampling period of",
                "the data acquisition system to the smallest recorded",
                "pulse baseline width of 1.2 ns, - 8.3%;",
                "  the energy resolution of the detector system which",
                " is 168 keV FWHM, that is 1.6% in the measurement at",
                " 14.3MeV and 1.3% in the measurement at 17.0MeV."
              ]
            }
